# Practice 6: Python File Handling and Built-in Functions

## Project structure

Practice6/
├── file_handling/
│   ├── write_files.py
│   ├── read_files.py
│   ├── copy_delete_files.py
│   └── sample.txt
├── directory_management/
│   ├── create_list_dirs.py
│   └── move_files.py
├── builtin_functions/
│   ├── map_filter_reduce.py
│   └── enumerate_zip_examples.py
└── README.md

## Topics covered

- File modes: r, w, a
- Reading files: read(), readline(), readlines()
- Writing and appending files
- Context manager: with
- File and path operations: os, shutil, pathlib
- Directory management
- Built-in functions: len(), sum(), min(), max(), map(), filter(), reduce(), enumerate(), zip(), sorted()
- Type checking and conversions

## How to run

### File handling
python file_handling/write_files.py
python file_handling/read_files.py
python file_handling/copy_delete_files.py

### Directory management
python directory_management/create_list_dirs.py
python directory_management/move_files.py

### Built-in functions
python builtin_functions/map_filter_reduce.py
python builtin_functions/enumerate_zip_examples.py